summary: SummaryMAC Skinfinish Sunstruck Matte Bronzer is a soft matte bronzer powder that adds warmth and depth. MAC Sunstruck Bronzer is designed to enhance your natural skin tone, this buildable and blendable creamy powder features double-processed pigments for a vibrant finish.

reviews.headline: Perfect powder bronzer
reviews.comments:
I have searched for a bronzer powder that would not be drying on my skin, or too heavy to blend easily.
This one has finally did the trick.

reviews.headline: Nice texture
reviews.comments: I think I chose the wrong color. Other than that, the formula is nice. Will go back and purchase the correct color.

reviews.headline: Would NOT Recommend ï¿¼
reviews.comments: Smells horrible. Even if the color and application was great, I would not use because of the smell.

reviews.headline: yes
reviews.comments: Love this goes on so smooth!! Great Product!!
this product gives the perfect glow if you wo be tan or rosy. With no orange undertone.

reviews.headline: Hard panâ€¦.
reviews.comments: So I have a problem with this bronzer powder I set my face and even through setting my face this bronzer will hit hard pan. I have had to scrape the top part with a spoon countless times. I'm finally returning it because it is a huge waste of money once it hits hard pan it doesn't even work. It's really frustrating because it is a beautiful color and a beautiful formula when freah but unfortunately I suppose with my face routine, it doesn't fit in.

reviews.headline: I like it!
reviews.comments: I was just wandering around Ulta when I found this bronzer unexpectedly. I found the shade I liked, tried it, and decided to get it. I do like it a lot! It lasts a really long time, has a good formula, and I like the color. The only thing is that you need to put a lot on if you want it to show and it is hard to get the right amount on you at first! Still, I really like this bronzer and can't find another one with the same or really similar color that is better.

reviews.headline: I've purchased this product twice.
reviews.comments: I love this product !  I purchased twice, and it broke both times.  Not sure I would buy again.

reviews.headline: Terrible smell, had to throw away
reviews.comments: I loved this bronzer at first. It had the best coverage and was super blendable but after a few months it seemed like it hsd expired or something. The smell was terrible and the compact started looking odd. I decided to toss. After reading others reviews I found out I wasnt the only one! Maybe it was the formulation?

reviews.headline: Meh
reviews.comments: Packaging is super cute.  Im nc35/40 in summertime and got the matte deep golden. Pigment is there but it seems kinda dusty instead of creamy. Doesnt seem to last all day but it is 115 f days now. Maybe i needed a warmer tone. Blends ok. Pat mcgrath is way better for $9 more.

reviews.headline: I just can't get around the smell
reviews.comments: When it arrived, it had an aroma of parmesean cheese. I tried letting it air out, wiping it with alcohol, but the smell persists. I think it's a strong powder or talc smell, but it just smells funky and feel like I can also smell it on my face, even a month later. This is the first MAC product I have purchased.

reviews.headline: smell is bad
reviews.comments: bronzer is nice and right amount of glow but the smell is bad. it smells like if it has expired already. And the top layer of the product has started to get nasty and I havent had it for a long time.

reviews.headline: love this bronzer
reviews.comments: this is a great color for that sun kissed look - just enough for a perfect glow and easy to apply

reviews.headline: Don't buy!!!
reviews.comments: The smell is so bad I can't even use it. Too late to return! Mac needs to give everyone's money back! DO NOT BUY!

reviews.headline: For the price it's meh
reviews.comments: The price is so high for such terrible packaging the top looks like a gum wrapper and it does smell bad like when u leave crayons in the heat but the color is nice ao im a keep it you do look super pretty bronze! They need to lower their prices or stick to the black sleek packaging

reviews.headline: Good old reliable MAC!
reviews.comments: I was using IT bronzer prior the MAC, but they were out of stock. So I opted to go with MAC since it was a product I used 25 years ago. The quality never ceases to amaze me. Good coverage and it doesn't settle in my under eye wrinkles ðŸ™‚. Definitely a repurchase down the road and I would highly recommend this product.

reviews.headline: Why does it smell like that?!
reviews.comments: To gain a perspective, I normally wear NC40 in foundation color. I purchased this and Nars Talc-Free in Laguna to compare, because it was recommended by an Ulta employee. Buildable, but I don't need two of the same color and it has a putrid smell up close. Returning it.

reviews.headline: Love
reviews.comments: I've never used bronzer. I was shown how to apply it with a brush and loved the natural peach tones. It goes along with my red hair

reviews.headline: Returned
reviews.comments: Way too expensive to have no pigment. Returned

faceoff_positive.comments:
If you're in pursuit of that sun-kissed look, SKINFINISH SUNSTRUCK Matte Bronzer is a must-have addition to your makeup arsenal. This bronzer effortlessly delivers a natural, matte finish that enhances your complexion without looking overdone.

One of the standout features of this bronzer is its buildable formula, allowing you to achieve your desired level of warmth and contour with ease. Whether you're aiming for a subtle glow or a more defined sculpted look, this product adapts beautifully to your preferences.

The finely milled texture of the bronzer ensures smooth and seamless application, blending effortlessly into the skin for a flawless finish. Its long-lasting formula means you can enjoy your sun-kissed radiance throughout the day without the need for constant touch-ups.

What truly sets SKINFINISH SUNSTRUCK Matte Bronzer apart is its versatility. Not only does it excel at bronzing, but it also doubles as a fantastic contouring product, adding depth and dimension to your features.

As for packaging, the sleek and compact design makes it perfect for on-the-go touch-ups or travel. Plus, the inclusion of a mirror is a convenient bonus.

In summary, SKINFINISH SUNSTRUCK Matte Bronzer is a game-changer for anyone seeking a natural, matte bronzed look. With its buildable formula, seamless application, and versatility, it's sure to become a staple in your makeup routine.
faceoff_positive.headline: A Must Have!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I bought this because my previous "radiant matte bronzing powder" was discontinued. This product is more expensive, smaller, and smells terrible. The compact also feels very cheap compared to my old one. The color is very similar, which is the only good thing I have to say. 

The price I can understand since it's taken so long to get through my previous bronzer, but the smell is inexcusable. I don't know if it's the product itself or if the product absorbed the smell of the cheaper plastic but it is really foul. The smell does seem to get better after a bit, but it doesn't make me want to put the product on my face at all. My previous MAC bronzer basically had no smell at all.
faceoff_negative.headline: What happened?
